---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/Projects.astro";
import GitWrapperImg from "../../assets/images/gitwrapper.png";
import BrainIcon from "../../assets/icons/brain.astro";
import GithubIcon from "../../assets/icons/github.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
import { projects } from "../../pages/index.astro";

const links = [
  {
    icon: GithubIcon,
    url: "https://github.com/laincodex/gitwrapper",
    label: "View source on Github",
  },
];
---

<Layout title="GitWrapper">
  <ProjectLayout
    title="GitWrapper"
    image={GitWrapperImg}
    links={links}
    techStack={projects[5].tech_stack}
  >
    <div slot="description">
      GitWrapper is a CLI tool I made in Rust to wrap the git command to be able
      to use another ssh key without adding it to the key agent. <br /> This way,
      you can use a different private ssh key file while using a git repository.
    </div>
    <Article title="How it works">
      <BrainIcon slot="icon" />
    </Article>
    <p class="mb-5">
      Imagine the situation where you are in your work's computer and you need
      to download a private repository you own. Using this wrapper you don't
      need to create a new ssh key or import to the computer's key agent, you
      just simply configure this wrapper to use your key.
      <br />
      <br />
    </p>
    <p class="my-5">
      <br /><br />
    </p>
  </ProjectLayout>
</Layout>
